Felix Falk Carlebach (15 April 1911 in Lübeck - 23 January 2008 in Manchester) was a German-born  British rabbi in Manchester, England.
He was an honorary citizen of the city of Lübeck and had both German and British citizenship.

response: The synagogue has a number of charismatic leaders, including for many years Rabbi Felix Carlebach, Chazan Solomon Morris and more recently Rabbi Yitzchok Rubin. That tradition of vibrant leadership was later continued by Rabbi Dovid Lewis and Chazan Michael Isdale.
** Felix Carlebach (1911–2008), Rabbi in Manchester, England
